            <title>[FLINK-28018] the start index to create empty splits in BinaryInputFormat#createInputSplits is inappropriate</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-28018</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;when the number of created split is smaller than the minimum desired number of file splits, &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/blob/master/flink-core/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/api/common/io/BinaryInputFormat.java#L150&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;BinaryInputFormat.java#L150&lt;/a&gt; use `&lt;em&gt;&lt;b&gt;files.size()&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/em&gt;` as the start index to create empty splits. That is inappropriate, the start index should be `&lt;em&gt;&lt;b&gt;inputSplits.size()&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/em&gt;`.&#160;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
